E1S3AUD.original: ~z~Bad news, Mr. Congressman. Something more important than your career has come up and I can't help you.
E1S3AUD.translated: ~z~坏消息，议员先生。我突然有些比你的政治生涯更要紧的事，帮不了你了。

E1S3AUD.original: ~z~Oh, appreciate the heads up and the friendly patter. Another time, Johnny.
E1S3AUD.translated: ~z~哦，感谢你毫无意义的友情提示。那就下次吧，Johnny。

E1S3AUD.original: ~z~Find some other putz to clean up your shit, Mr. Stubbs. I've decided I'm busy.
E1S3AUD.translated: ~z~擦屁股这事您还是另请高明吧，Stubbs先生。我说过我很忙了。

E1S3AUD.original: ~z~Ouch, Klebitz. Let a fellow down easy.
~z~While your work ethic needs much improvement, Klebitz, you can always be relied upon for your charm.
E1S3AUD.translated: ~z~虽然你的职业素养有待提高，Klebitz，但能力确实值得信赖。

E1S3AUD.original: ~z~Oh sure, champ. Thanks for letting me know. You have yourself a wonderful time.
E1S3AUD.translated: ~z~哦好吧，能人。多谢你通知。祝你玩得开心。

E1S3AUD.original: ~z~Hey, Stubbs, did you really want that thing done? Too bad, 'cause something else came up.
E1S3AUD.translated: ~z~嘿，Stubbs，你真的想那么做吗？很遗憾，我突然有点急事。

E1S3AUD.original: ~z~Oh, you're a hard nose, Klebitz. I'll give you that.
~z~Mr. Congressman. I can't do that thing right now. Deal with it.
E1S3AUD.translated: ~z~议员先生。我现在没法替你办事。面对现实吧。

E1S3AUD.original: ~z~Hey, Mr. Stubbs, working for you makes me feel like a piece of shit. I can't do that thing for you. Sorry.
E1S3AUD.translated: ~z~嘿，Stubbs先生，替你做事让我感觉很糟。我不能为你做那件事。抱歉。
